# Lessons Learnt 

  * round robin assignment helped - decrease latency - from 5 to 1.4 
  * using global DSQ for enqueuing in enqueue and consuming in dispatch helped - decrease latency - from 1.5 to 1.4
  * directly dispatching to local_cpu from enqueue is better then global case 
  * should use atomic fetch_add for rr stuff 
  * decreasing ts from 200ms to 20 ms helped - didn't change latency 

  * enqueue can get called even if all dispatches are local from select_cpu - still don't know why? - ext.c says it would happen if select_cpu skipped dispatch to local dsq 

  * it's more important to find next available cpu then to let the task run 
    * in this context there are alot of interdependent parallel tasks
